<br>
I'm not talking about Symbol of Marzin - I'm talking about Marzin's Mark.  Once your guild has a few, druids start to MGB again (in the guilds I've had experience with that have copies of Marzin's Mark).<br>
<br>
Every single one of our players is over the usable AC cap from their armour's raw ac, for their agility; ac decreases of 35 mean (literally) nothing to them - they're so far over the usable cap it's humourous.  I think Lotusfly has about 350 more visible item ac than is usable with her buffed agility.  Heh.  Ditto rangers, warriors, and so on.<br>
<br>
Marzin's Mark (not Symbol of Marzin) + Protection of the Glades gives everyone the extra hit points.  That's the main reason that it's used; though the mana regen is a nice side effect.  Most pure casting classes used to get PotG before anyway, but this way even the hybrids get it, too.<br>
<br>
That's just a handy aside to the fact that it provides extra hit points, though.  ^_^<br>
<br>
Recall when the DR Flower from the Plane of Mischief used to give a little extra stamina or so?  That translated into about 10-20 hits, depending on your class.  Everyone, during that time, used to have their DR Petals up.  They'd spend a buff slot for a tiny quantity of hits.<br>
<br>
The argument that people don't want to lose a buff slot in order to get the much more significant extra hit points from PotG + Marzin's Mark is a little thin.  ^_~<br>
<br>
These are the people that buy Metabolism 3, so that their Halas 10lb Meat Pies, and Misty Thicket Picnics, can be giving the extra 20-30hp + stamina for as long as possible.  Hit points are craved.  ;)<br>
<br>
<br>
Toodlepip,<br>
<br>
Rebecca <p><img src="http://www.keepersofthefaith.org/images/kitty.gif" align="right">
